<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-20T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-20T11:00:00-05:00" n="700" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d700">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">660f.116Auto/22: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gittings</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-20T17:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">March 20,
                                        1928—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 20—1:05
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>21. Department’s No. 9, March 15, 5 p.m. It now appears that information
                            was premature because no licenses actually granted yet. I am requesting
                            expedition and will promptly inform Department. Full report by mail.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gittings</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>